<Content>Drenched in Sun and Beauty Congratutlations to Hilton !!! This resort is another example of why I can count on the Hilton Brand. This resort is a high end four star resort. The staff is always trying to help you, and that is hard to do, when almost everything we needed was automatically provided. After an arrival with a bump or two we were assigned a great suite. our stay was in mid-March with abundant sunshine and record temperatures for March. We were there to relax and enjoy the Valley of The Sun... Enjoy we did with a Capital E Say hello to Shawn at the fornt office. He is the best example of refined hospitality we have encountered in recent years. Get his recommendations for restaraunts in the area that are super. Try the adult pool just off the lobby and enjoy poolside dining from the Mexican Restaraunt serving the pool. The view resembles Tuscany in Italy with resort buildings climbing the mountainside drenched with sun and shaded by Palm Trees. We extended our stay two additional days before trecking off to Sedona. Tip: Make sure to always check the temps and weather in Sedona before leaving Phoenix. Climbing up to 4,400 feet can provide a few surprises. We experienced cold and wet weather after having just leaving Phoenix and a two hour drive. This resort is loaded with pools and fun things to do. Take the mountain hike for great views of the region. Have fun and enjoy ! We did and will return soon. 
